text: Eureiandra balfourii is a species of plant in the family Cucurbitaceae. It is endemic to Yemen. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical dry forests. ==References== Category:Endemic flora of Socotra balfourii Category:Vulnerable plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot Category:Taxa named by Isaac Bayley Balfour Category:Taxa named by Alfred Cogniaux
